com.hcl.domino.design

Interface DbDesign


  • public interface DbDesign
    Provides access to a database's design elements, allowing querying, selection, and creation.

      • getFileResource

        Optional<FileResource> getFileResource(String name)
        Retrieves the named file resource.

        Note: this method uses the value of the "$TITLE" field of the design element, not the "$FileNames" of the file resource. These may diverge, such as when a file resource has an alias assigned to it.

        Parameters:
        name - the name of the resource to restrict to
        Returns:
        an Optional describing the FileResource, or an empty one if no such element exists
        Since:
        1.0.24

      • getFileResources

        Stream<FileResource> getFileResources()
        Retrieves all file resource design elements in the database.
        Returns:
        a Stream of FileResources
        Since:
        1.0.24

      • getScriptLibrary

        Optional<ScriptLibrary> getScriptLibrary(String name)
        Retrieves the named script library. This library will be of a specific subtype based on its language.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the library to restrict to
        Returns:
        an Optional describing the ScriptLibrary, or an empty one if no such element exists
        Since:
        1.0.24
        See Also:
        JavaLibrary, JavaScriptLibrary, ServerJavaScriptLibrary, LotusScriptLibrary

      • getScriptLibraries

        Stream<ScriptLibrary> getScriptLibraries()
        Retrieves all script library design elements in the database. These libraries will be of a specific subtype based on their language.
        Returns:
        a Stream of ScriptLibrary subclass elements
        Since:
        1.0.24
        See Also:
        JavaLibrary, JavaScriptLibrary, ServerJavaScriptLibrary, LotusScriptLibrary
